  "prompt": "How do you install fonts in Debian Xfce using the command line?",
  "response": "To install fonts in Debian Xfce using the command line, you can follow these methods:\n\n1. Using apt (system-wide installation):\n```bash\nsudo apt install fonts-[fontname]\n```\nExample:\n```bash\nsudo apt install fonts-liberation\n```\n\n2. Manual installation for a single user:\n```bash\nmkdir -p ~/.local/share/fonts\ncp /path/to/font/files/*.ttf ~/.local/share/fonts\nfc-cache -fv\n```\n\n3. System-wide manual installation:\n```bash\nsudo mkdir -p /usr/local/share/fonts\nsudo cp /path/to/font/files/*.ttf /usr/local/share/fonts\nsudo fc-cache -fv\n```\n\n4. Install from .deb file:\n```bash\nsudo dpkg -i font-package.deb\n```\n\n5. Using font manager:\n```bash\nsudo apt install font-manager\n```\n\nAfter installation, you can list installed fonts with:\n```bash\nfc-list\n```\n\nRestart your application or log out and log back in to see the new fonts.",
